beer.beer_description: Long Haul, a California IPA collaboration with Rocky Ridge in Western Australia, features a dry-hopped blend of El Dorado, Citra, Nelson Sauvin SubZero Hop Kief, and Nectaron. After a year of refinement, it boasts crystal-clear clarity, releasing a burst of hops upon opening. The aroma offers hints of dank west coast hops, while the palate delights with overripe tropical and stonefruit flavors, despite its lean malt bill. It culminates in a satisfying bitterness and a touch of white wine spritz, evoking a taste of California without the need for a long flight.
